[Screaming]

1012
01:23:59,064 --> 01:24:00,528
This is it, Mom.

1013
01:24:00,667 --> 01:24:03,571
The Madonna and child,
on the island of Aghtamar,

1014
01:24:03,709 --> 01:24:05,051
where it all began.

1015
01:24:06,750 --> 01:24:09,206
I was there
when they shot that scene.

1016
01:24:11,234 --> 01:24:14,138
It was the same day
she attacked the painting.

1017
01:24:14,276 --> 01:24:15,968
The painting based on this.

1018
01:24:17,542 --> 01:24:19,431
I left for Turkey a week later.

1019
01:24:19,560 --> 01:24:22,016
- Does she know
you went to the island?

1020
01:24:22,153 --> 01:24:24,042
- Who?
- Your mother.

1021
01:24:24,171 --> 01:24:26,114
- No. No, she doesn't.

1022
01:24:27,661 --> 01:24:29,288
- Have you spoken to her?

1023
01:24:29,422 --> 01:24:30,765
- No.

1024
01:24:36,595 --> 01:24:38,286
- People lose touch.

1025
01:24:47,258 --> 01:24:49,267
- There's something
l've been meaning to ask you.

1026
01:24:49,404 --> 01:24:50,746
- Yeah?

1027
01:24:52,799 --> 01:24:54,457
- Aren't there dogs
used forthis sort of thing?

1028
01:24:54,591 --> 01:24:56,349
- What sort of thing?

1029
01:24:56,481 --> 01:24:58,752
- Well, if you think
there are drugs in these cans...

1030
01:24:58,882 --> 01:25:00,858
- Yeah, we have dogs forthat.

1031
01:25:05,096 --> 01:25:07,781
- So, uh...
why don't you use one?

1032
01:25:07,913 --> 01:25:09,321
- What?
- A dog.

1033
01:25:10,859 --> 01:25:15,881
- A dog would take away
what I like most about this job.

1034
01:25:16,015 --> 01:25:18,155
- What's that?
- The opportunity to...

1035
01:25:18,289 --> 01:25:21,193
better understand
how the mind works.

1036
01:25:22,931 --> 01:25:24,973
A dog would come in and bark.

1037
01:25:25,109 --> 01:25:27,053
And that bark would mean
only one thing:

1038
01:25:27,191 --> 01:25:28,501
That there were drugs
in these cans.

1039
01:25:28,631 --> 01:25:32,660
Ruff! You're lying.
I caught you. You're a liar.

1040
01:25:35,772 --> 01:25:37,716
That's what a dog does.

1041
01:25:37,854 --> 01:25:39,164
- Right.

1042
01:25:39,294 --> 01:25:42,493
- L'm not saying that
what a dog does isn't important.

1043
01:25:42,624 --> 01:25:44,033
But there are...

1044
01:25:44,162 --> 01:25:47,230
other issues involved.
Aren't there?

1045
01:25:49,477 --> 01:25:51,716
Things a dog doesn't have
the capacity to consider.

1046
01:25:53,257 --> 01:25:55,362
A dog...

1047
01:25:55,498 --> 01:25:57,987
wouldn't know
he's being retired,

1048
01:25:58,124 --> 01:26:00,493
that this is his last day,

1049
01:26:00,621 --> 01:26:03,012
his final interrogation.

1050
01:26:07,186 --> 01:26:09,195
Is someone picking you up?

1051
01:26:09,332 --> 01:26:11,242
- No.

1052
01:26:11,381 --> 01:26:13,237
- Good.

1053
01:26:13,366 --> 01:26:14,927
Might be worried.

1054
01:26:16,600 --> 01:26:19,319
Even l'm worried.

1055
01:26:19,451 --> 01:26:21,786
- About what?

1056
01:26:21,915 --> 01:26:23,259
- About you.

1057
01:26:27,040 --> 01:26:28,535
What are we gonna do?

1058
01:26:30,082 --> 01:26:31,906
There's no one I can contact.

1059
01:26:34,085 --> 01:26:37,153
There's no way of confirming...

1060
01:26:37,286 --> 01:26:41,480
that a single word that
you've told me tonight is true.

1061
01:26:43,787 --> 01:26:47,270
- Everything l've told you
is exactly what happened.

1062
01:27:23,110 --> 01:27:26,244
- My mother never told me about
what happened during the march.

1063
01:27:26,376 --> 01:27:30,154
Only one story.
They had a pomegranate tree

1064
01:27:30,284 --> 01:27:31,691
in the garden.

1065
01:27:31,821 --> 01:27:34,572
And when they came
to take the family away,

1066
01:27:34,703 --> 01:27:37,574
she grabbed one of the fruit.

1067
01:27:37,713 --> 01:27:40,911
She knew the journey
would be long.

1068
01:27:41,043 --> 01:27:46,513
Every day, she would take out
one seed and eat it.

1069
01:27:46,647 --> 01:27:50,195
She would bite it bit by bit,

1070
01:27:50,330 --> 01:27:53,813
pretending that one seed
was a whole meal.

1071
01:27:56,862 --> 01:27:58,291
Try it.

1072
01:28:13,449 --> 01:28:16,932
Now, when I eat
a pomegranate seed,

1073
01:28:17,068 --> 01:28:19,655
it gives me two things:

1074
01:28:19,790 --> 01:28:22,475
Luck

1075
01:28:22,608 --> 01:28:24,648
and a powerto imagine.

1076
01:28:30,101 --> 01:28:31,826
[Beeping]

1077
01:28:37,721 --> 01:28:39,032
- Hello?

1078
01:28:39,163 --> 01:28:41,816
- Mom. Hi.

1079
01:28:41,950 --> 01:28:44,635
- Raffi?

1080
01:28:44,767 --> 01:28:47,737
Raffi, where are you?
- Ljust got back to Toronto.

1081
01:28:47,873 --> 01:28:50,557
They've stopped me here
at Customs,

1082
01:28:50,691 --> 01:28:52,831
with all the footage
I got forthe film.

1083
01:28:54,374 --> 01:28:56,065
They're wondering
what's inside the cans.

1084
01:28:56,199 --> 01:28:57,509
- What cans?

1085
01:28:57,640 --> 01:28:59,845
What are you talking about?

1086
01:28:59,977 --> 01:29:02,630
- The stuff I had to shoot
around Van.

1087
01:29:02,763 --> 01:29:05,765
They've stopped me here
at Customs and, uh...

1088
01:29:05,901 --> 01:29:08,140
they want to open the cans,
but they can't. Because...

1089
01:29:09,488 --> 01:29:11,759
Raffi, do you want me to lie?

1090
01:29:11,826 --> 01:29:13,420
- Yes.

1091
01:29:15,284 --> 01:29:16,779
I miss you too.

1092
01:29:19,478 --> 01:29:22,197
I have so much to tell you, Mom.

1093
01:29:22,329 --> 01:29:24,752
I went to Aghtamar.
- Aghtamar?

1094
01:29:24,890 --> 01:29:28,122
- I found the mother and child
on the church.

1095
01:29:28,253 --> 01:29:30,743
I had some days free,
so I went to Aghtamar.

1096
01:29:30,879 --> 01:29:33,085
Here, l'm gonna hand
you overto the inspector.

1097
01:29:33,217 --> 01:29:35,836
I think he wants to know more
about the film this is for.

1098
01:29:35,970 --> 01:29:39,967
- Hello. Are you Raffi's mother?
- Yes, I am.

1099
01:29:40,101 --> 01:29:42,591
- Are you a professor
at the university?

1100
01:29:42,728 --> 01:29:44,485
- Yes, that's right.

1101
01:29:46,154 --> 01:29:47,464
- And you're involved
in this film?

1102
01:29:47,594 --> 01:29:50,825
- Yes, I was hired
as a historical consultant.

1103
01:29:50,957 --> 01:29:53,064
A book I wrote
was used as a reference.

1104
01:29:53,198 --> 01:29:55,206
- What was the book about?

1105
01:29:55,343 --> 01:29:58,542
- It was about the life
of Arshile Gorky.

1106
01:29:58,674 --> 01:30:00,650
- Is he the main character
in the film?

1107
01:30:00,787 --> 01:30:02,098
- No.

1108
01:30:02,229 --> 01:30:04,783
- What was your son shooting
in Turkey?

1109
01:30:04,918 --> 01:30:08,019
- He had to go to the place
where Arshile Gorky was born.

1110
01:30:08,153 --> 01:30:09,463
- Why?

1111
01:30:09,594 --> 01:30:13,044
- To shoot some material.
- And how is this material

1112
01:30:13,180 --> 01:30:14,522
to be used?

1113
01:30:16,991 --> 01:30:19,065
- To help show what happened.

1114
01:30:21,154 --> 01:30:23,709
- How did he die?

1115
01:30:23,843 --> 01:30:25,885
- Who?

1116
01:30:26,021 --> 01:30:28,357
- Gorky.

1117
01:30:28,487 --> 01:30:31,719
- Why are you asking me
these questions?

1118
01:30:31,849 --> 01:30:34,184
- Did he kill himself?

1119
01:30:38,318 --> 01:30:40,522
[Cheering and clapping]

1120
01:30:58,844 --> 01:31:02,010
- Ani, we have to go.

1121
01:31:02,142 --> 01:31:03,900
- Where are you?

1122
01:31:04,032 --> 01:31:05,855
- Where am I?

1123
01:31:05,984 --> 01:31:10,298
- Listen, she's at the premiere
of the film,

1124
01:31:10,436 --> 01:31:13,668
and she'II have to get back
to you, okay?

1125
01:31:13,798 --> 01:31:17,096
- Hello? May I speak
to my son, please?

1126
01:31:19,722 --> 01:31:21,862
- So the film
is completely finished.

1127
01:31:26,959 --> 01:31:30,344
- Please, let me speak to my son.

1128
01:31:34,580 --> 01:31:36,272
Raffi?

1129
01:31:39,096 --> 01:31:40,438
- Yeah.

1130
01:31:40,985 --> 01:31:42,547
Tell me what to do.

1131
01:31:47,293 --> 01:31:49,204
- Sure.

1132
01:31:49,343 --> 01:31:51,166
L'II meet you at home.

1133
01:32:22,646 --> 01:32:24,688
- Marty, how are you responding
to the people

1134
01:32:24,824 --> 01:32:27,159
who say this is all
an exaggeration?

1135
01:32:27,289 --> 01:32:29,330
- It's, you know...
it's documented.

1136
01:32:29,467 --> 01:32:31,257
And really, every word I say

1137
01:32:31,388 --> 01:32:33,462
is directly quoted
from Ussher's own journal.

1138
01:32:33,597 --> 01:32:34,907
- Marty!

1139
01:32:35,647 --> 01:32:36,924
- That's where I met them,
right on the train.

1140
01:32:37,120 --> 01:32:39,030
- To Ararat.
- Yeah. They were shooting

1141
01:32:39,169 --> 01:32:40,480
a commercial.
- A commercial?

1142
01:32:40,610 --> 01:32:42,782
- I became friends with the
cameraman and I told him

1143
01:32:42,916 --> 01:32:45,339
that I wanted to get an image
with this. This.

1144
01:32:45,477 --> 01:32:47,846
I wanted to get a shot of Ararat
in the picture.

1145
01:32:47,976 --> 01:32:49,285
- What for?
- Forthe film. I thought

1146
01:32:49,416 --> 01:32:51,589
it was something we could use.
- How? The film is finished.

1147
01:32:51,722 --> 01:32:53,032
- I wasn't thinking about that.

1148
01:32:53,162 --> 01:32:55,881
He had to bribe a soldier
to take us up.

1149
01:32:56,013 --> 01:32:58,633
That's a military road, okay?
You can't just go up there.

1150
01:32:58,766 --> 01:33:01,802
That's his voice. You can
actually hear it on the...

1151
01:33:01,937 --> 01:33:04,656
We went up about halfway and
then... We shot this footage

1152
01:33:04,787 --> 01:33:06,927
from there. On film.
On this film.

1153
01:33:07,060 --> 01:33:10,096
- Why didn't you tell me
this before?

1154
01:33:10,231 --> 01:33:12,272
- I had to tell you
the other story.

1155
01:33:12,407 --> 01:33:13,521
- Why?

1156
01:33:13,657 --> 01:33:17,337
- Because it meant
something to me.

1157
01:33:30,981 --> 01:33:33,601
- So this voice on the tape,

1158
01:33:33,735 --> 01:33:35,908
this crew person,

1159
01:33:38,345 --> 01:33:40,868
gave you the film,

1160
01:33:41,004 --> 01:33:42,598
let you use his camera,

1161
01:33:42,734 --> 01:33:44,228
bribed a soldier...

1162
01:33:45,808 --> 01:33:48,078
and then drove you up
Mount Ararat.

1163
01:33:49,618 --> 01:33:50,961
- Yes.

1164
01:33:52,660 --> 01:33:55,761
- Did he ask you to do him
a favour in return?

1165
01:33:55,894 --> 01:33:57,520
- Who?

1166
01:33:57,656 --> 01:33:59,446
- Raffi...

1167
01:34:01,370 --> 01:34:06,195
Did he ask you to bring anything
into this country?

1168
01:34:12,225 --> 01:34:14,267
- He asked me to bring
those cans.

1169
01:34:32,463 --> 01:34:33,894
- And what's in them?

1170
01:34:35,826 --> 01:34:38,316
- He said it's film.

1171
01:34:38,452 --> 01:34:41,716
- Why did you believe him?

1172
01:35:30,360 --> 01:35:31,703
- Ani.

1173
01:35:33,242 --> 01:35:34,584
Ani!

1174
01:35:46,435 --> 01:35:48,192
[Screaming]

1175
01:36:58,036 --> 01:37:00,340
- Close the door.

1176
01:37:21,670 --> 01:37:23,099
- Can we turn out the light?

1177
01:37:24,647 --> 01:37:25,957
- Why?

1178
01:37:26,088 --> 01:37:28,359
- So the film won't be ruined.

1179
01:37:28,490 --> 01:37:30,979
- You're still convinced.

1180
01:37:32,524 --> 01:37:35,396
- You can feel it in the dark.

1181
01:37:35,534 --> 01:37:39,148
- All right, Raffi.
Turn out the light.

1182
01:37:58,014 --> 01:37:59,902
Forthe last time,

1183
01:38:00,031 --> 01:38:02,848
what do you think is in here?

1184
01:38:02,977 --> 01:38:04,321
- Film.

1185
01:38:05,955 --> 01:38:08,413
That's what he told me.

1186
01:38:08,549 --> 01:38:10,623
That's what I need to believe.

1187
01:38:10,759 --> 01:38:13,127
- And what would happen
if you didn't believe it?

1188
01:38:15,625 --> 01:38:17,220
- L'd be a criminal.

1189
01:38:17,355 --> 01:38:20,424
- And what would you say
if I told you it was heroin?

1190
01:38:20,558 --> 01:38:22,763
- It isn't.

1191
01:38:22,895 --> 01:38:25,417
- What makes you so sure?

1192
01:38:25,553 --> 01:38:27,496
- You'd turn the light on.

1193
01:39:31,135 --> 01:39:33,656
- Sir? The arrivals?
The international arrivals?

1194
01:40:56,986 --> 01:40:58,580
- You let him go?

1195
01:40:58,715 --> 01:41:00,058
- Yep.

1196
01:41:02,046 --> 01:41:04,348
- But what was in the cans?

1197
01:41:04,479 --> 01:41:06,455
- Would you believe me
if I told you?

1198
01:41:06,592 --> 01:41:08,634
- What do you mean?

1199
01:41:08,770 --> 01:41:10,112
- Heroin.

1200
01:41:11,652 --> 01:41:13,311
- No.
- Film?

1201
01:41:16,135 --> 01:41:18,046
- But I don't get it.

1202
01:41:18,185 --> 01:41:20,904
You did check the cans.
- Yeah. One.

1203
01:41:22,571 --> 01:41:23,881
- What was in it?

1204
01:41:24,013 --> 01:41:27,594
- Ah, it doesn't matter,
for Chrissake.

1205
01:41:27,727 --> 01:41:29,517
- Dad!

1206
01:41:31,570 --> 01:41:35,150
- I trusted him.
- But he was lying to you

1207
01:41:35,285 --> 01:41:36,594
all night. He...

1208
01:41:36,725 --> 01:41:38,515
He changed his story.

1209
01:41:38,647 --> 01:41:42,577
- The more he told,
the closer he came to the truth.

1210
01:41:42,714 --> 01:41:44,537
Till he finally told it.

1211
01:41:46,876 --> 01:41:49,081
I couldn't punish him
for being honest.

1212
01:41:49,214 --> 01:41:51,703
- But he was smuggling drugs.

1213
01:41:51,840 --> 01:41:53,532
- He didn't think he was.

1214
01:41:53,665 --> 01:41:56,350
- How do you know?

1215
01:41:56,483 --> 01:41:58,939
- He didn't believe
he could do something like that.

1216
01:42:03,016 --> 01:42:04,358
- Dad...

1217
01:42:08,812 --> 01:42:10,701
what came overyou?

1218
01:42:14,031 --> 01:42:15,755
- You did, Philip.

1219
01:42:19,891 --> 01:42:21,714
I was thinking of you.

1220
01:42:33,469 --> 01:42:34,484
- How are you responding
to the people

1221
01:42:34,557 --> 01:42:36,020
who say this is all
an exaggeration?

1222
01:42:36,159 --> 01:42:38,429
- This film is the kind of film-
- You have a visitor.

1223
01:42:38,560 --> 01:42:40,317
...you can do only once
in your lifetime.

1224
01:42:40,450 --> 01:42:44,030
Because it tells a story
which is a true story...

1225
01:42:58,863 --> 01:43:01,516
- Arshile Gorky was born
in a small village

1226
01:43:01,649 --> 01:43:05,132
on the shores of Lake Van.

1227
01:43:05,267 --> 01:43:07,308
From the shores of this village,

1228
01:43:07,444 --> 01:43:10,315
the island of Aghtamar
was in plain view.

1229
01:43:10,454 --> 01:43:12,343
Gorky, as a child,

1230
01:43:12,471 --> 01:43:14,164
would go to this island
with his mother,

1231
01:43:14,297 --> 01:43:16,502
who would show him
the detailed carvings

1232
01:43:16,634 --> 01:43:18,130
on the walls of the church.

1233
01:43:20,894 --> 01:43:23,131
- Why are you showing this to me?

1234
01:43:23,263 --> 01:43:25,818
- This is the origin,
from the memory of this place,

1235
01:43:29,443 --> 01:43:32,959
right to the photograph,
to the sketch,

1236
01:43:33,094 --> 01:43:34,405
to the painting.

1237
01:43:34,535 --> 01:43:36,510
You told me to go there.

1238
01:43:36,648 --> 01:43:39,203
I had to put something in my
heart. If that was gonna happen,

1239
01:43:39,338 --> 01:43:41,761
it was gonna happen here.

1240
01:43:43,725 --> 01:43:46,247
That I was prepared
to throw my whole life away.

1241
01:43:49,970 --> 01:43:53,355
And last night,
as we were sitting in that...

1242
01:43:53,492 --> 01:43:55,827
dark room,

1243
01:43:55,957 --> 01:43:57,813
as I heard him open the can,

1244
01:43:57,943 --> 01:44:00,792
I felt it.

1245
01:44:00,921 --> 01:44:02,930
- You felt what?

1246
01:44:04,491 --> 01:44:07,286
His ghost.

1247
01:44:07,422 --> 01:44:09,791
The ghost of my father.

